That sounds like an extremely important discovery, Laurie.
If you have found that recorders are sensitive to some radio
frequencies, and those recorders and those frequencies have not been
well tested or documented, then potentially some recorders are also
senstive to normal AM/FM, as well as other frequencies.  This should
bring into serious question any EVPs people have gotten, unless they
know those sensitivies beforehand.


